                           Codd. Laurent. tom. ii. col. 589> § iv-</note>-->
                        <incipit><supplied>C</supplied>rebras ex te literulas</incipit>
                        <explicit>sis innocentum. Valle. M<ex>edio</ex>l<ex>ani</ex>i v junii.</explicit>
                        <!-- Ep fam XX 4? -->
                     </msItem>
                     <msItem n="6"><locus from="18v" to="20r">(fols. 18v–20r)</locus>
                        <author key="person_39382430">Petrarch</author>
                        <title key="work_3563">Letter to Giovannolo da Mandello</title>
                        <incipit> <supplied>S</supplied>era quidem amice optime ad epistoIam vestram</incipit>
                        <explicit>nos in patria et in terra viuentium videamus. Valete feliciter et immerite exul et <sic>eregie</sic>. Ticini vi Jullii frater vester si quid est. </explicit>
                        <listBibl>
                           <bibl> Ernest H. Wilkins and Giuseppe Billanovich, 'The Miscellaneous Letters of Petrarch', <title>Speculum</title>, 37, No. 2 (Apr., 1962), 226-243 at pp. 232-3</bibl>
                        </listBibl>
                     </msItem>
                     <msItem n="7">
                        <locus from="20r" to="86v">(fols. 20r–86v)</locus>
                        <author key="person_39382430">Petrarch</author>
                        <title key="work_3567">Secretum</title>
                        <incipit><supplied>A</supplied>thonito mihi quidem</incipit>
                        <explicit>fortuna non obstrepat. Explicit liber iste. Deo gratias amen.</explicit>
                        <note>Fols. 86(a)r-v, 86(b)r-v ruled but blank.</note>
                     </msItem>
